===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|suffixum||suffix|lang=la}}, from {{term|sub||under, beneath|lang=la}} + {{term|fixus|lang=la}}, perfect passive participle of {{term|figere||to fasten, fix|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{qualifier|noun}} {{IPA|/ˈsʌfɪks/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-suffix.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
* {{qualifier|verb}} {{IPA|/ˈsʌfɪks/|/səˈfɪks/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|ɪks|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

# One or more letters or sounds added at the end of a word to modify the word's meaning.
#: ''The '''suffix''' "-able" changes "sing" into "singable".''
# {{context|mathematics|lang=en}} A [[subscript]].

====Usage notes====
* The plural {{term|suffices|lang=en}} occasionally appears (including in one educational publication), but it is not a standard Latin plural.

